  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d9a\u0dc5 \u0dba\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd4\u0db8 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Increasing the electricity bill is a must",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Electricity and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekera said in Parliament today (29) that although the increase in electricity bills is difficult for the people, looking at the board's expenses, this is something that must be done.",
        "He said this during the adjournment debate regarding the government's decision to increase the electricity bill.",
        "The minister mentioned that more than 7600 crore rupees have to be paid to the Electricity Board for renewable energy projects and private power plants and the amount to be paid to the Petroleum Statutory Corporation alone is 3100 crore rupees.",
        "He also said that although the electricity bill has been increased, relief has been provided to the low income earners.",
        "Mr. Wijesekera said that some of the tasks that could be done by the Electricity Board had been assigned to other departments in the past.",
        "He said that there are serious issues regarding the salaries and allowances of the employees of the Electricity Board and the Petroleum Statutory Corporation and that these institutions give the employees a 25 percent salary increase annually without any service evaluation."
      ],
